Fans of Afrobeat and Afropop genres, have gone wild with joy after some nigerian songs was recently appreciated by two international football stars.
In a viral video that made the rounds on social media, Manchester United forward, Jesse Lingard was captured dancing to Asake’s monster hit song, Sungba.
The football star vibed to Sungba in a car as he described it as a fun moment on Snapchat.
SEE THE VIDEO HERE
A number of Fans reacted to the video of Lingard dancing to Asake’s song with admiration.

SEE REACTIONS BELOW

 
Still on Nigerian Afrobeat getting a global  recognition, Barcelona striker, Memphis Depay in a clip shared on his Instastory, was all smiles as he sang along and made body movements in rhythm to the beats of Young John’s song titled Dada.
It was gathered that Depay and his teammate were celebrating their return to Netherlands’ national team in the viral video.
SEE THE VIDEO HERE
Nigerians on social media have been known to love recognition especially when it is from international stars and this time was not any different.

